Restrictions on insider selling have expired in waves. A limitation on more than 200 million shares expired on Oct. 29.

COST OF SHORTINGPivotal Research Group analyst Brian Wieser said he did not expect Facebook insiders to sell all of their shares as the lockups expired.

'I would expect heavy volumes over the next few weeks, but not undigestible volumes,' said Wieser.

By his estimate, roughly 486 million of the nearly 800 million newly freed Facebook shares will be sold.

There is some evidence that the heavy interest in 'shorting' the stock was dissipating, given the poor performance since it first sold shares in May.

